## How the agent should work in this repo

- Plan before code. Show the plan inline and wait for explicit approval.
- One responsibility per file. Refactor before extending a file past 500 lines.
- Log architectural choices via `/bencium-decide` (or append to `.harness/archive/` manually if the plugin isn't installed).
- Failed verify or deploy → run `/bencium-retro` (or write a postmortem to `.harness/archive/NNNN-retro-*.md`).

## When the bencium-harness plugin is installed

Slash commands available: `/bencium-init`, `/bencium-next`, `/bencium-verify`, `/bencium-deploy`, `/bencium-decide`, `/bencium-feature`, `/bencium-promote`, `/bencium-retro`, `/bencium-rollback`. Skills auto-load context and watch for architectural decisions.
